text.section:
Before a certificate expires, a medication technician periodically may renew it for an additional term, if the certificate holder:
Otherwise is entitled to be certified;
Submits to the Board a renewal application on the form that the Board requires;
Pays to the Board a renewal fee set by the Board;
Every 2 years, provides satisfactory evidence of completion of a Board-approved clinical refresher course; and
Provides satisfactory evidence of completion of 100 hours of practice as a certified medication technician within the 2-year period preceding the date of renewal.

section.section:
On receipt of the criminal history record information of a certificate holder forwarded to the Board in accordance with § 8-303 of this title, in determining whether to renew the certificate, the Board shall consider:
The age at which the crime was committed;
The circumstances surrounding the crime;
The length of time that has passed since the crime;
Subsequent work history;
Employment and character references; and
Other evidence that demonstrates whether the certificate holder poses a threat to the public health or safety.
